Man jumps from balcony of Romanian parliament
Romanian Prime Minister Emil Boc has survived the latest no-confidence motion against his government, in the most dramatic of circumstances. His speech to parliament was interrupted by a man jumping from the balcony in protest at austerity measures. Identified as a state television employee, the man was wearing a T-shirt with the words: "You killed our children's future." Media reports say he may have lost benefits for the care of his autistic son. ... http://www.euronews.net/